			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Magnet Media Inc.</strong> is a digital content marketing firm and video production company based in New York City, with offices in San Francisco, Chicago and Seattle. Magnet produces global video and social media campaigns for the largest brands in the world, including but not limited to Google/YouTube, TED, Chase, Microsoft, Adobe, Comcast, The Associated Press, ABC, NBC, Showtime Networks, The Sundance Channel, The Tribeca Institute and many more.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Magnet Media is looking to fill the role of a part or full time Business Development Intern to support the most senior Account Executive based out of the NY office.</p>
<p>
<br />
The Business Development Intern calls for someone passionate about digital media specifically as it relates to content marketing across the media, technology, entertainment and finance verticals. Ideal candidates must have the ability to communicate effectively, work autonomously as well as collaboratively and apply a high level of integrity to all projects.</p>
<p>
This is an excellent opportunity for full-time employment, as this department is growing rapidly within the organization. Should this candidate deliver an exceptional performance in all key areas there will be a discussion around full-time options upon internship completion.</p>
<p>
<br />
Compensation will be discussed during the interview and will be decided on based on the candidate.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Specific daily activities will include:</p>
<p>
<br />
1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Research across various blogs and media outlets; creation of research packets and one-sheets on both vertical and account-specific information</p>
<p>
<br />
2. Assisting in the process of campaign planning - could include brainstorming sessions for specific titles, brands and/or big picture strategy recommendations</p>
<p>
<br />
3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identifying target contacts within designated Tier 1 Accounts</p>
<p>
<br />
4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outreach to target contacts via email or phone on a daily basis to secure meetings and/or calls</p>
<p>
<br />
5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accompanying Account Executive on calls and meetings to help provide insights based on industry news and trends</p>
<p>
<br />
6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Providing notes and background information on various companies for Account Executive&#39;s preparation and review</p>
<p>
<br />
7.&nbsp; Managing initial correspondence with client prospects and research on additional targets in those fields</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Requirements:</p>
<p>
-Minimum: Bachelor&#39;s Degree from a 4-year college or university. Ideal majors include Marketing, Advertising, Business or related field.</p>
<p>
<br />
-Strong interest and/or experience in content marketing&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<br />
-Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with extensive knowledge of web and social media. Keynote, Word and Excel proficiency is a plus</p>
